<br>
Ok. Here's a quick little list of my solo path for my warrior ... who is currently level 51, agnostic halfling, with 2 AAs. Keep in mind I didn't solo the entire time. I got groups when I could, but I solo'd when I couldn't.<br>
<br>
1 to 10 Misty Thicket. Kinda Duh there, but ... you know.<br>
<br>
10 to 13 West Commonlands.<br>
<br>
13 to 15 Oasis<br>
<br>
15 to 24 I grouped in Paludal Caverns. Sorry, but the XP was just too good to even worry about whether it was solo or grouped or whatever.<br>
<br>
24 to 26 Solo in Paludal<br>
<br>
26 to 30 Marus Seru ... the easy mobs. The Greyhoppers and the Zelniaks and the Lightcrawlers. I steered clear of the Stonegrabbers except when I got in groups.<br>
<br>
31 to 45 ... Here's the kicker ... I DID solo each and every one of these levels almost exclusively barring ONE group and ONE duo session, but the entire time was spent in the SAME zone ... Dawnshroud Peaks (I was working on Seru faction, so I just sort of stuck around, and I really liked the zone).<br>
<br>
Anyways that gets me to 45, where your question kicks in ...<br>
<br>
45 to 48 solo ... Dreadlands, Mountain Giant Fort. But if that don't do it for ya, try FV frogs and dogs, or Frontier Mountains, or Overthere. Kunark is just GOOD for soloing mid to late 40s.<br>
<br>
48 to 51 ... Lake of Ill Omen. Get an EB item. You SHOULD have an EB item by level 50. It's sort of helpful. Get the item, go kill Bloodgills. They're great XP easy to solo. HOWEVER, if you don't have an EB item ... go kill Kobolds in Sol B, or Frogs in LGuk. Good god, the XP in the OLD OLD world is sooooo easy to get at these levels, and it's everywhere.<br>
<br>
51, +2 AAs ... Glacier Yetis in DL, and the occasional groupage. Then I got ballsy and started using my ToD and have been doing Plaguebone Thieves, and Drolvarg Ragers in DL, but really, Glacier Yetis are the best bet.<br>
<br>
Now, I've spent most of my life soloing with my monk (now 60) ... and can assure you that if my monk could kill this crap solo your warrior can too ... it'll just take longer ...<br>
<br>
SOL B.<br>
<br>
Live it, learn it, LOVE it.<br>
<br>
Go from Kobolds, to bats, to bats and bugs, to LDCs. You can bleed Sol B DRY. My monk dinged 52, 54, 55, 56, 57 and 58 all in Sol B.<br>
<br>
It's a dungeon. You NEED to be careful and you need certain things to solo properly. You do NOT need to be outrageously twinked, but it helps. But you do need to be ready to die, ready to run, and have a good working knowledge of the zones. And then you need to figure out how to escape and how to deal with runners.<br>
<br>
There's a ton of different options though. This is just the path I've taken. (Oh yeah, after 58 ... Velk's Lab). But you can do Twilight Sea ... Scarlet Desert ... The Grey ... Emerald Jungle ... Trakanon's Teeth ... heck go back to Dawnshroud Peaks and kill Rockhoppers ... whatever. There's TONS of dark blue mobs out there to fight. Find em, kill them.<br>
<br>
For warriors to Solo, IMO, you need a Truncheon of Doom, a great damaging 2hander (high DPS you need to solo with, but it's better to NOT have to take as much riposte damage), a haste item, LOTS of bandages, and either JBoots or SoW potions. Minimum. Now you can get ALL of this stuff cheap these days.<br>
<br>
For warriors to solo BETTER, an invig BP helps. Regen items help. A snare proccing weapon helps. Damage Shield item/potions (think 8th coldain ring for instance). That way the mob helps you kill itself. Gate potions help. Insta-cast gate potions help. A fast horse is better than a SoW potion. Run 3 is best of all. Lifetap proccing weapons can really offset the damage you take, so they help. See, you can solo with a bare bones setup, but the more time you spend getting items that HELP you solo, the better you will solo. It's the annoying facts of EQ, sadly. But items, yes, will help.<br>
<br>
Just remember, it's POSSIBLE, no matter what your level of gear, to solo. Soloing can be done, no matter what your budget is but ... soloing is SLOW and BORING as hell.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
-Wubao <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baruchthebarbarianbastard>baruch the barbarian bastard</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://images.diary-x.com/users/translucent/sirnot.JPG" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/03 12:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3115.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://images.diary-x.com/users/translucent/sirnot.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmmmm ...</span><hr size=1> Sol B is my current hunting grounds. Bats are tremendously easy and still con mostly db to my 53 druid tagalong. <br>
