Beo  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=burarum>Burarum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/03 12:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3115.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_exp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Soloing</span><hr size=1> I've only tried soloing a few times as a warrior, but at around level 40 I found some great xp soloing in dawnshroud.  I'm a lizzy so the regen may have helped a little bit, probably by an unnoticeable amount though.  Doing large zelniaks, which conned db, I could easily take one down and lose only a bubble or so of hp, (I had around 2k at the time).  In about 20 or so minutes I had gotten a full bubble of exp, whereas I would have gotten about a quarter of that amount in a decent group in the dreadlands or great divide.  I'm sure there's a bunch little spots like this in the game that can give you decent exp soloing, right?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taminy>Taminy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/03 12:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3115.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing</span><hr size=1> In some ways, unless you do have very high end gear warrior soloing can be a waste of time. For someone who plays in shorter sessions and has trouble finding a group it's better than nothing though if done right.<br>
<br>
I agree with what some people have said about required soloing gear. However, one thing I disagree about is that soloing = dying. With the right mentality, you shouldn't die a lot. You will probably waste a lot of time though.<br>
<br>
What you want to do is always play it safe. If you think you might die, run. You will lose time on this - often beating a mob nearly to death, then you get an add and end up zoning with almost no hps. This wastes time, bandages, etc and you have nothing to really show for it. You also may risk training another person or persons so try your best not to (shout a warning and do not path your train near known camp spots if at all possible). <br>
<br>
I've found this to often be the case when I 2box my shaman. Most of the time that I die I could (and should) have just cut my losses and ran or used some other escape technique. Even if you're using a 2boxed cleric you still probably want to run if you think there's a decent chance you will die because of mana recovery (especially if the cleric dies and you have to res yourself). <br>
<br>
As I said before though, this does take a certain type of mentality. You must not be lazy, overconfident, or greedy.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glatius2>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 913<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/03 12:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3115.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_exp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Soloing</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I'm sure there's a bunch little spots like this in the game that can give you decent exp soloing, right?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
